latestPosts.caption: Send this to someone who wants their dream body but eats Maggi for every Meal!🍝 @indiasyogagirl

We all know too much sugar isn’t good for us. It’s not just in sweets and desserts. 

It’s hiding in your morning bread, your ketchup, your sauces, and even so-called “healthy” drinks. 

Packaged juices, sodas, sweetened teas… they’re loaded with added sugar that our body simply doesn’t need.

Instead, choose natural options like lemon water, coconut water, or just plain water with a few herbs or fruits added in. Your body will feel so much lighter, cleaner, and more energized!

#SurbhiGandhi Yoga, Surbhi Gandhi

My mom once dreamt of becoming a doctor.

But growing up in a traditional Marwadi joint family, that dream didn’t stand a chance. 

It wasn’t that she lacked talent or ambition. It’s just that the world around her didn’t give women that freedom.

But she always made one thing clear: her daughter would never need permission to dream BIG and do WHATEVER she wants. (except getting into relationships🤪) 

She never questioned my choices- whether I wanted to become a CA, switch to yoga and wellness, create content, or take the road less travelled.

Most of the things I have learnt about Health and Diet are from her. 

It was because of her that I started my Yoga Journey! 

She missed weddings, celebrations, and so many outings just to be with me during my CA exams.

I hated the fact that she never did Anything for herself. But Always for Family and Relatives. 

I’ve seen her give So endlessly. She always puts everyone first, managing the house and somehow never asking for anything in return.

All that I’ve been able to do is because of her quiet strength and endless support. She does it all so effortlessly. Always with a smile.

I hope I make her proud💖

Happy Mother’s Day!
